original_sql: SELECT COUNT(*)  FROM table_3 WHERE column_22 >= DATE '2019-01-01'   AND column_22 < DATE '2021-01-01';
rewritten_sql: SELECT COUNT(*)  FROM (     SELECT column_22,      ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY column_22) AS row_num      FROM table_3 ) t1 WHERE t1.row_num >= 1 AND t1.column_22 < DATE '2021-01-01' AND t1.column_22 >= DATE '2019-01-01';

original_sql: SELECT column_1, COUNT(*) FROM table_3 GROUP BY column_1 ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 20;
rewritten_sql: SELECT      column_1,     COUNT(*) AS count FROM      table_3 GROUP BY      column_1 ORDER BY      count DESC LIMIT 20;

original_sql: SELECT      MIN(column_6),     MAX(column_6),     AVG(column_6) FROM table_3;
rewritten_sql: SELECT      MIN(column_6) AS min_column_6,     MAX(column_6) AS max_column_6,     AVG(column_6) AS avg_column_6 FROM (     SELECT column_6 FROM table_3 GROUP BY column_6 ) AS temp;

original_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM table_3 WHERE column_6 > 0;
rewritten_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM table_3 AS t3 WHERE column_6 > 0;
